Each entity and each foreign entity authorized to transact business in this Commonwealth shall deliver to the Secretary of State for filing an annual report that sets forth:
The name of the entity or foreign entity and the state or country under whose law it is organized;
The address of its registered office and the name of its registered agent at that office in this Commonwealth;
The address of its principal office; and
With respect to each:
Corporation, not-for-profit corporation, cooperative, association, or limited cooperative association, whether domestic or foreign:
The name and business address of the secretary or other officer with responsibility for authenticating the records of the entity;
The name and business address of each other principal officer; and
The name and business address of each director;
Manager-managed limited liability company, whether domestic or foreign, the name and business address of each manager;
Limited partnership, whether domestic or foreign, the name and business address of each general partner;
Business trust, whether domestic or foreign, the name and business address of each trustee; and
Professional service corporation, domestic or foreign, a statement that each of the shareholders, not less than one-half (1/2) of the directors, and each of the officers other than secretary and treasurer is a qualified person.

The requirement to file an annual report shall not apply to:
A limited partnership governed as to its internal affairs by the Kentucky Uniform Limited Partnership Act as it existed prior to its repeal by 1988 Ky. Acts ch. 284, sec. 65;
A partnership other than a limited liability partnership that has filed a statement of qualification pursuant to KRS 362.1-951 or a foreign limited liability partnership;
A foreign rural electric cooperative or foreign rural telephone cooperative not required to qualify to transact business by a filing with the Secretary of State; or
An unincorporated nonprofit association that has not filed a certificate of association.
